DELLA FULWOOD v. STATE OF FLORIDA 12 So. (2nd) 772

January Term, 1943

April 6, 1943 Division A Frank F. UEngle and Thomas M. Linton, for appellant. J. Tom Watson, Attorney General, and Woodrow M. Melvin, Assistant Attorney General, for appellee. PER CURIAM:

This appeal is from a conviction of murder in the second' degree and questions only the sufficiency of the evidence. We find the evidence ample to sustain the verdict, hence the judgment is affirmed.

BUFORD, C. J., TERRELL, CHAPMAN and ADAMS, JJ., concur.
